# Nginx Reverse Proxy and Load Balancer Lab (RHEL/CentOS/Rocky Linux)

## Lab Setup

| Machine                       | IP            |
| ----------------------------- | ------------- |
| Web Server 1                  | 192.168.25.10 |
| Web Server 2                  | 192.168.25.20 |
| Reverse Proxy / Load Balancer | 192.168.25.30 |

Replace IPs according to your environment.

---

# Part 1: Configure Web Server 1

## Install Apache

```bash
yum install -y httpd
```

## Enable and Start Service

```bash
systemctl enable httpd
systemctl start httpd
```

## Create Web Page

```bash
echo "<h1>Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10</h1>" > /var/www/html/index.html
```

## Open HTTP Port

```bash
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http
firewall-cmd --reload
```

## Disable SELinux

Temporary:

```bash
setenforce 0
```

Permanent:

```bash
sed -i 's/^SELINUX=.*/SELINUX=disabled/' /etc/selinux/config
```

Verify:

```bash
getenforce
```

Output:

```text
Permissive
```

