# Part 3: Configure Reverse Proxy Server

## Install Nginx

```bash
yum install -y nginx
```

## Enable and Start

```bash
systemctl enable nginx
systemctl start nginx
```

## Open HTTP Port

```bash
firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=http
firewall-cmd --reload
```

## Disable SELinux

```bash
setenforce 0
sed -i 's/^SELINUX=.*/SELINUX=disabled/' /etc/selinux/config
```

---

# Configure Reverse Proxy

Edit:

```bash
vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
```

Inside `http {}` add:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://192.168.25.10;
    }

    location /pune {
        proxy_pass http://192.168.25.20;
    }
}
```

---

## Test Configuration

```bash
nginx -t
```

Expected:

```text
syntax is ok
test is successful
```

Reload:

```bash
systemctl restart nginx
```

