# Part 4: Configure Load Balancer

Edit nginx configuration:

```bash
vi /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
```

Inside `http {}`

```nginx
upstream backend_servers {
    server 192.168.25.10;
    server 192.168.25.20;
}

server {
    listen 80;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend_servers;
    }
}
```

---

## Restart Nginx

```bash
nginx -t
systemctl restart nginx
```

---

# Test Load Balancing

Run multiple times:

```bash
curl http://192.168.25.30
```

Example Output:

```text
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
```

Next request:

```text
Web Server 2 - IP: 192.168.25.20
```

Next request:

```text
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
```

Round Robin is the default algorithm.

---

# Part 5: Configure Weighted Load Balancing

Edit nginx configuration:

```nginx
upstream backend_servers {
    server 192.168.25.10 weight=7;
    server 192.168.25.20 weight=1;
}

server {
    listen 80;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://backend_servers;
    }
}
```

---

## Reload Nginx

```bash
nginx -t
systemctl restart nginx
```

---

# Test Weight

Send 8 Requests

```bash
for i in {1..8}
do
curl -s http://192.168.25.30
echo
done
```

Expected Pattern:

```text
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
Web Server 2 - IP: 192.168.25.20
```

Count Requests:

```bash
for i in {1..16}
do
curl -s http://192.168.25.30
done | sort | uniq -c
```

Expected:

```text
14 Web Server 1 - IP: 192.168.25.10
 2 Web Server 2 - IP: 192.168.25.20
```

This confirms the **7:1 weighted load balancing** configuration.
